  "answer": "**Nāradasmṛti**, Chapter 1, contains this argument.[^1]\n\nThe text states: \"Therefore, examination is proper. (Nar. M1.62) **The sky appears like a surface, a firefly like a fire. But there is no surface in the sky, nor is there fire in a firefly. (Nar. M1.63)** Therefore, even a matter seen with one's own eyes should be properly examined.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Nāradasmṛti, [Chapter 1](/works/unknown-naradasmrti-7650d2/01/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Nāradasmṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-naradasmrti-7650d2/01/translation/#p-4363ef).",
